== English ==

=== Pronunciation ===
:bâr'ĭng

=== Noun ===
:'''Bearing'''
# A mechanical device that supports another part and/or reduces [[friction]]. 
# A [[beam]], [[column]], or other device that carries weight.
# A measurement of location, taken from one point to another, usually by [[compass]].
# A relationship or connection, as in ''That has no bearing on this issue''.

=== Adjective ===
# (Architecture) A structure designed to support a load, as in ''load bearing wall''.

=== Verb ===
'''Bearing, to [[bear]]'''
# Carrying or transporting, as in ''Beware of Greeks bearing gifts''.
# The act of producing fruit or offspring.